Great question! Here‚Äôs a detailed comparison to clarify what Citrix DaaS Monitor covers versus what uberAgent provides, especially across the 7 phases I outlined.
Citrix DaaS Monitor vs. uberAgent: Coverage by Phase
Phase	Area	Citrix DaaS Monitor Coverage	uberAgent Coverage	Notes
1	Logon Times (high-level)	‚úîÔ∏è (basic total logon duration)	‚úîÔ∏è (full breakdown)	Citrix: high-level only; uberAgent: detailed (GPO, scripts, profile, etc.)
2	Application Performance	‚ùå	‚úîÔ∏è (per-app, per-user)	Citrix: no per-app analytics; uberAgent: startup time, hangs, per-process metrics
3	Session/Protocol Slowness	‚úîÔ∏è (session/ICA latency, RTT, etc.)	‚úîÔ∏è (more detail)	Citrix: basic protocol stats; uberAgent: adds channel breakdown, deeper analysis
4	Resource Contention	‚ùå	‚úîÔ∏è (detailed)	Citrix: only "resource errors" (very basic); uberAgent: per-process, per-user, GPU
5	Network Quality (endpoint-side)	‚ùå	‚úîÔ∏è (if enabled)	Citrix: no endpoint-side; uberAgent: measures from VDA or endpoint if needed
